                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.61/27b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-23T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 23, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>722. In thousands of dollars for March, 1941, exports of United States
                    merchandise to the Soviet Union, 3,590; re-exports, 647; imports of merchandise
                    from the Soviet Union for consumption in the United States, 4,264. Three months
                    total for these classifications, 15,423; 978; and 6,889 respectively. All
                    figures are preliminary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
